--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL

To compile the operating system, run the <build.sh> script in the <etc>
directory. A disk image will be produced that can be used via all the normal
manners of installing an operating system to hardware or a VM. If it doesn't
compile on your system, open a ticket upstream in the code repository.

To see possible build arguments, use the "-h" switch when running the build
script.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DEPENDENCIES

Aster requires quite a few things to be bootable on your hardware (and may still
fail if all these conditions are met);

- ALL MODES
  - An x86_64 processor. This may also be referred to as AMD64.
  - A BIOS or UEFI-capable motherboard. Nearly all motherboards ever
    manufactured should have at least a BIOS (sometimes referred to as Legacy
    Boot).
- BIOS MODE
  - ACPI-compliance without serious bugs or imperfections, usually contained in
    BIOSes after January 1st, 2001.
  - VESA/DDC-compliance of recommended version 2Ab.
  - VESA/VBE-compliance of at least version 2.0.
  - Support for the INT 15, AX=E820 memory mapping interrupt. This nearly always
    accompanies any BIOS after 2002.
- UEFI MODE
  - Not supported yet!

NOTE: Aster is experimental! While at a very small chance, it may damage your
system on boot attempt. Into the forseeable future, booting in a virtual machine
is always the reccommended approach.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
